defaultBoth parents undertaking joint responsibility for childcare is unusual. Traditionally it is still 
defaultthe husband 
defaultwho 
defaulttakes on the role of primary breadwinner and therefore the hours available 
defaultfor the woman to
default work need to fit arou
defaultnd the timetable of first the child and secondly the husband
default – even when nursery care is available. The logistics of childcare provision and working hours can be difficult to balance. In general, it was felt that finding a job that fitted around childcare 
defaultseriously restricted the hours available to work. As a consequence, women gradu
defaultates often take on the role of 
defaultteaching assistants, as the hours fit in with family life and school holidays. This can be seen as having a positive benefit in that this might be
default a way of influencing the next generation to at least embark on a STEM career.
