defaultThe problem of retaining females in STEM subject areas is s
defaulteen as being related to 
defaultthe insecurity of short term contracts, the perception that future promotion opportunities would be biased against females and that they would not be treated fairly and as equals. The situation was seen as being further aggravated b
defaulty the ‘two-body’ problem – ie the difficulty of two partners in a relationship seeking professional jobs in a similar geographic location; often compromise
default is needed and this tends
default to be made by the female.
