defaultOne suggestion was that there should be better careers advice from school and throughout subsequent employment.
default Based on the evidence that girls do better in STEM subjects when taught in single sex classes the possibility of single sex sixth forms was suggested. However as there appears to be more peer pressure against girls doing STEM subjects in mixed sex schools
default this may be too little too late.
defaultAt University level the
default provision of more funding for longer-term fellowships
default was seen as the way forward. It should be emphasised that these would need to be
default advertised widely to raise awareness among
default all women in academia, and be 
defaultopen to both 
defaultmale and female applicants 
defaultto prevent them being
default seen as a second-class option.
